# <type>(<scope>): Summary in imperative, start lowercase, no period
# Example: feat(auth): add oauth login flow
# Keep it under 50 chars. ############################# 50 chars is here #

# Common types (Conventional Commits):
# feat:     new feature for the user
# fix:      bug fix
# chore:    maintenance, tooling, deps, configs (no logic changes)
# refactor: code changes that neither fix a bug nor add a feature
# docs:     documentation only
# style:    formatting only, no logic
# test:     add or update tests
# perf:     performance improvements

# Leave a blank line between title and body

# Body (optional): explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW.
# Wrap at 72 chars. ################################### 72 chars is here #

# You can reference issues:
# Closes #123
# Related to #456

# Leave one empty line before co-authors (if any)
# Co-authored-by: Name <email@example.com>